HEADWORD: Maieutics
<hw>Ma*ieu"tics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The art of giving
birth (<it>i. e.</it>, clearness and conviction) to ideas, which are
conceived as struggling for birth.</def> <rj><au>Payne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

